,0.092823,0.086788,0.067873,0.043605]},{"section":11,"text":"Her phosphate level is high.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033149,0.068019,0.089474,0.10043,0.10945,0.10851,0.10163,0.095331,0.087708,0.081372,0.067891,0.057027],"unified_progress":[0.040914,0.07923,0.095928,0.10428,0.10695,0.10193,0.10011,0.093299,0.086016,0.078718,0.065557,0.047077]},{"section":12,"text":"Phosphorus levels usually rise when the kidneys aren't filtering them out properly.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03254,0.064058,0.083508,0.10097,0.11179,0.11375,0.10789,0.10074,0.091639,0.077245,0.064042,0.051836],"unified_progress":[0.044631,0.083574,0.10125,0.10678,0.11152,0.10469,0.11235,0.08822,0.079878,0.069005,0.057789,0.040313]},{"section":13,"text":"High phosphate can lead to mineral metabolism disorders, and it can contribute to secondary hyperparathyroidism because the body tries to compensate by producing more PTH to increase calcium levels.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043407,0.059164,0.075538,0.090106,0.10181,0.10635,0.10683,0.10374,0.097345,0.084941,0.071962,0.058817],"unified_progress":[0.044037,0.073541,0.092339,0.09998,0.10617,0.10751,0.11101,0.093716,0.084528,0.076303,0.064104,0.046762]},{"section":14,"text":"Speaking of PTH, her levels are high.","dimension":6,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028352,0.058423,0.079748,0.090679,0.10187,0.10488,0.10141,0.099783,0.09436,0.094866,0.078911,0.066722],"unified_progress":[0.038694,0.075603,0.091395,0.10318,0.10502,0.10214,0.10439,0.093638,0.086101,0.082666,0.067746,0.04943]},{"section":15,"text":"Parathyroid hormone is released by the parathyroid glands and helps regulate calcium levels.","dimension":1,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039127,0.059624,0.077355,0.09311,0.1047,0.10825,0.10683,0.1023,0.095062,0.083027,0.070883,0.059728],"unified_progress":[0.04757,0.080576,0.097727,0.1039,0.10897,0.