n has electrolyte imbalances.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.076182,0.15349,0.073372,0.11287,0.10112,0.097377,0.082702,0.074511,0.066572,0.060794,0.054085,0.046918],"unified_progress":[0.097992,0.1277,0.07456,0.097192,0.093493,0.096094,0.084266,0.079822,0.074242,0.068584,0.060391,0.045668]},{"section":8,"text":"Low calcium and high phosphate make me think of mineral metabolism issues.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.050119,0.093376,0.10777,0.10849,0.10426,0.095303,0.09206,0.083503,0.075857,0.073204,0.062309,0.053745],"unified_progress":[0.061382,0.082503,0.092575,0.09817,0.10079,0.097618,0.095426,0.088532,0.082739,0.079778,0.067535,0.052956]},{"section":9,"text":"The PTH level is high.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047372,0.093036,0.10757,0.10882,0.10361,0.095385,0.093526,0.085803,0.078678,0.071713,0.06383,0.050661],"unified_progress":[0.065806,0.085938,0.097571,0.10211,0.10579,0.098443,0.10118,0.086426,0.078945,0.071077,0.060858,0.045858]},{"section":10,"text":"Wait, in chronic kidney disease, when the kidneys can't excrete phosphate properly, phosphate levels rise.","dimension":6,"group":2,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040706,0.080279,0.092926,0.10046,0.10339,0.1012,0.10046,0.093216,0.085007,0.079194,0.068536,0.054625],"unified_progress":[0.088652,0.080947,0.08995,0.094413,0.09826,0.098575,0.097675,0.089383,0.080099,0.073351,0.06146,0.047236]},{"section":11,"text":"High phosphate then suppresses calcitriol production and activates parathyroid hormone as part of the feedback loop.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042032,0.080007,0.090652,0.098161,0.10143,0.10045,0.10004,0.093127,0.084673,0.081743,0.068632,0.059061],"unified_progress":[0.050434,0.073563,0.09245,0.097748,0.1018,0.10431,0.10131,0.093402,0.086522,0.079154,0.066739,0.052566]},{"section":12,"text":"This leads to secondary hyperparathyroidism.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038945,0.075173,0.086185,0.09494,0.099759,0.099852,0.099737,0.093415,0.085468,0.08612,0.071702,0.068703],"unified_progress":[0.043639,0.064005,0.081461,0.091186,0.095816,0.10331,0.099488,0.09739,0.092397,0.087704,0.077329,0.066275]},{"section":13,"text":"The symptoms here\u2014hand pain.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048249,0.087096,0.090496,0.090966,0.091356,0.091257,0.090815,0.089856,0.085883,0.084863,0.078059,0.071105],"unified_progress":[0.060073,0.077948,0.081122,0.086659,0.090029,0.093301,0.091523,0.093371,0.090702,0.089594,0.080379,0.065298]},{"section":14,"text":"But the joints are normal on exam.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047233,0.090344,0.091576,0.089729,0.089264,0.091741,0.092138,0.092694,0.089957,0.083767,0.077602,0.063957],"unified_progress":[0.059852,0.081552,0.08496,0.089462,0.093185,0.093142,0.092774,0.0943,0.091242,0.087502,0.075173,0.056856]},{"section":15,"text":"Wait, secondary hyperparathyroidism can cause bone diseases like renal osteodystrophy.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034366,0.06939,0.081775,0.092706,0.099708,0.10125,0.1026,0.097013,0.090193,0.087318,0.076108,0.067571],"unified_progress":[0.043081,0.061012,0.081474,0.088309,0.094489,0.10497,0.10038,0.098444,0.094652,0.09022,0.07882,0.064153]},{"section":16,"text":"The bone pain might be from bone resorption due to high PTH.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027852,0.061602,0.075382,0.086892,0.096052,0.10081,0.10521,0.10131,0.097416,0.091303,0.084213,0.071966],"unified_progress":[0.058669,0.056412,0.06848,0.07739,0.087193,0.097322,0.096419,0.098378,0.098922,0.096526,0.090387,0.073901]},{"section":17,"text":"The classic bone changes in renal disease might include things like subperiosteal bone resorption in the fingers, which can cause pain.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032048,0.069646,0.081278,0.090942,0.096582,0.10084,0.10202,0.097439,0.096025,0.088435,0.077203,0.06754],"unified_progress":[0.044213,0.064955,0.082961,0.091057,0.097847,0.10143,0.10077,0.097519,0.095325,0.088203,0.074783,0.060942]},{"section":18,"text":"But the joints themselves aren't inflamed or tender, so it's more of a bone issue than arthritis.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035526,0.074616,0.084056,0.088954,0.091221,0.093829,0.096755,0.096179,0.095478,0.090703,0.082225,0.070459],"unified_progress":[0.038924,0.068124,0.079708,0.087876,0.094959,0.095399,0.096966,0.098632,0.097728,0.096189,0.081615,0.06388]},{"section":19,"text":"Other possibilities?","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031658,0.071735,0.092747,0.098729,0.098321,0.093041,0.092743,0.090843,0.088334,0.092412,0.078806,0.070632],"unified_progress":[0.033142,0.068985,0.082986,0.095857,0.09675,0.094881,0.10213,0.0963,0.092846,0.096876,0.07956,0.059685]},{"section":20,"text":"Maybe osteoporosis, but that's less likely in this context.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024274,0.058821,0.075154,0.084905,0.092513,0.096456,0.10265,0.10419,0.10165,0.099559,0.090832,0.068999],"unified_progress":[0.033243,0.063445,0.077556,0.084917,0.09406,0.096285,0.10017,0.10389,0.10114,0.10214,0.084438,0.058709]},{"section":21,"text":"Or maybe vitamin D deficiency, but that's part of the same pathway here.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027558,0.06251,0.077843,0.087153,0.094254,0.098413,0.10158,0.10151,0.098033,0.095675,0.08641,0.069052],"unified_progress":[0.044396,0.072519,0.083157,0.089795,0.094734,0.096877,0.098149,0.097856,0.094079,0.091523,0.078569,0.058345]},{"section":22,"text":"The key here is the combination of low calcium, high phosphate, and elevated PTH.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031238,0.066281,0.080926,0.088049,0.092088,0.093329,0.096729,0.095079,0.094143,0.093222,0.089791,0.079126],"unified_progress":[0.045795,0.06726,0.08046,0.087859,0.094598,0.097011,0.098498,0.094783,0.092847,0.090387,0.083069,0.067434]},{"section":23,"text":"That's the classic triad for secondary hyperparathyroidism in chronic kidney disease.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032076,0.064116,0.076761,0.086556,0.092614,0.094599,0.097052,0.0941,0.090801,0.092491,0.08563,0.093203],"unified_progress":[0.038726,0.056281,0.071762,0.081298,0.087399,0.095744,0.095311,0.09688,0.096047,0.094651,0.093199,0.092702]},{"section":24,"text":"The hand pain could be due to the bone changes from the high PTH.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023654,0.053823,0.068205,0.080788,0.091853,0.098409,0.10519,0.10316,0.10148,0.0966,0.093442,0.083398],"unified_progress":[0.058811,0.048648,0.059308,0.068061,0.07926,0.092089,0.092938,0.098879,0.10323,0.10516,0.10428,0.089333]},{"section":25,"text":"So putting it all together, the most likely diagnosis is secondary hyperparathyroidism.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028901,0.051808,0.059508,0.066402,0.072998,0.078262,0.084858,0.089336,0.095635,0.099979,0.10954,0.16278],"unified_progress":[0.030781,0.036729,0.045736,0.055065,0.059911,0.074237,0.07776,0.092213,0.10421,0.109,0.13835,0.176]},{"section":26,"text":"The lab results align perfectly with that.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031912,0.066073,0.081829,0.086563,0.085787,0.083455,0.086389,0.08724,0.09001,0.097336,0.094453,0.10895],"unified_progress":[0.029184,0.049613,0.060004,0.071437,0.076189,0.08268,0.087091,0.094683,0.10196,0.11035,0.11641,0.12041]},{"section":27,"text":"The patient's on dialysis, which doesn't fully correct phosphate levels, leading to this imbalance.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038527,0.071387,0.078828,0.084839,0.090206,0.09569,0.095633,0.095306,0.093104,0.092368,0.086005,0.078107],"unified_progress":[0.063722,0.080574,0.077503,0.077603,0.081618,0.085985,0.087519,0.09241,0.091963,0.092043,0.089782,0.079278]},{"section":28,"text":"Yeah, that makes sense.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.31539,0.051761,0.052567,0.06155,0.063636,0.064085,0.062858,0.069235,0.069415,0.067016,0.069744,0.052744],"unified_progress":[0.21202,0.085425,0.063566,0.063205,0.073396,0.072739,0.0868,0.079884,0.07696,0.064194,0.060432,0.061376]}]}}